 family, love, abandonment, and ultimately, forgiveness and reconciliation. It is also a spellbinding detective story-steeped in racial politics and the troubled history of two continents-of one man's search for the truth behind the enigmas of his, and his mother's, lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAfrican AmericansvBiography. 0aAfrican AmericansxBiography. 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rightsxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthern States. 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rightszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aApartheidxSouth Africa. 0aApartheidzSouth Africa. 0aBrothers and sisters. 0aCivil rights movementsxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthern States. 0aCivil rights movementszSouthern StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aGeography. 0aHistory. 0aHouze, David. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931749423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520931749.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles